27 September 2014The Inter-Ministerial Task Team on the Nigeria tragedy led by Minister Jeff Radebe will brief the media on the developments following the collapse of a building at the Synagogue Church of All Nations in Lagos, Nigeria. This is part of government s commitment to keep the South African public abreast on the situation. Members of the media are invited as follows: Date: Sunday, 28 September 2014 Time: 16h00 Venue: GCIS Head Office, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Frances Baard Street, Hatfield, Pretoria NB: There will be a video-link to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament, Cape Town. RSVP: Mmemme Mogotsi (Pretoria) Cell: 072 856 4288 E-mail: Mmemme@gcis.gov.zaMzimasi Ngqelu (Cape Town) Cell: 076 904 3557 E-mail: Mzi@gcis.gov.za Enquiries: Phumla Williams Acting GCIS CEO Cell: 083 501 0139Issued by Government Communication (GCIS) on behalf of the Inter-Ministerial Task Team on the Nigerian tragedy 